reviewText: I recommend this product to viewers who long for more elegance and less gore in their detective stories.  The plots are well constructed, the  decor is in good taste and Angela Lansbury is a pleasure to watch, even if sometimes her character (like other main characters in other series--- Miss Marple, Poirot, James Bond, etc) is introduced a bit artificially.But, once the plot is launched, it is all suspense and eminently enjoyable.I am delighted that this series is now available to the public.  I have been looking for it for a number of years. At last, I have the whole series, that is to say a lot of enjoyment ahead of me.
summary: A welcome return to a bit of nostalgia

reviewText: I can't really add anything to the other reviews. Angela Lansbury is great, as always, and the episodes are entertaining. Many times I can figure out 'who-dunnit', but sometimes I can't, so it keeps things interesting. I do kind of wish they didn't have the "bonus episodes" from the following season - then you have less to watch the next time.

reviewerName: K. Goyette "A voracious reader and experiment...
reviewText: Five disc set, 21 episodes with a bonus episode "Amsterdam Kill", Season 11. We were late in the game in discovering Murder She Wrote but have successfully obtained all the seasons that are released and we like to re-watch our favorites--which is pretty much all of it! Excellent writing, really good plot twists, funny characters--especially those with the painfully obvious fake Maine accents! If you're a fan of Murder She Wrote, you will want to add this to your collection!
summary: If you're a fan, you'll love this season also!

Title: Murder, She Wrote: The Complete Tenth Season

reviewText: I always have enjoyed "Murder She Wrote" and now I have another season in my collestion!Wonderful stories of murder and a rather reluctant Jessica Fletcher/crime solver/writer, a series that celebrates one womens crime solving abilities when the police and other branches of the law fall short in their investagations. I Love it when her light bulb moments happen and always try to figure out who-done-it with her. I'm amazed somtimes at who the culprit turns out to be. I also get a lot of laughs, that balance out the drama well. Always there to help out a friend in need, set in many locations around the world. Wonderful in my eyes. Something I can watch without all the blood, gore and sexual mess of so many detective programs of today.
Title: Murder, She Wrote: The Complete Tenth Season
